    "note": "<p>In the first sample, we are given a polynomial <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>P</i>(<i>x</i>)\u2009=\u200910\u2009-\u20099<i>x</i>\u2009-\u20093<i>x</i><sup class=\"upper-index\">2</sup>\u2009+\u20095<i>x</i><sup class=\"upper-index\">3</sup></span>.</p><p>Limak can change one coefficient in three ways:</p><ol> <li> He can set <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>a</i><sub class=\"lower-index\">0</sub>\u2009=\u2009\u2009-\u200910</span>. Then he would get <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>Q</i>(<i>x</i>)\u2009=\u2009\u2009-\u200910\u2009-\u20099<i>x</i>\u2009-\u20093<i>x</i><sup class=\"upper-index\">2</sup>\u2009+\u20095<i>x</i><sup class=\"upper-index\">3</sup></span> and indeed <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>Q</i>(2)\u2009=\u2009\u2009-\u200910\u2009-\u200918\u2009-\u200912\u2009+\u200940\u2009=\u20090</span>. </li><li> Or he can set <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>a</i><sub class=\"lower-index\">2</sub>\u2009=\u2009\u2009-\u20098</span>. Then <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>Q</i>(<i>x</i>)\u2009=\u200910\u2009-\u20099<i>x</i>\u2009-\u20098<i>x</i><sup class=\"upper-index\">2</sup>\u2009+\u20095<i>x</i><sup class=\"upper-index\">3</sup></span> and indeed <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>Q</i>(2)\u2009=\u200910\u2009-\u200918\u2009-\u200932\u2009+\u200940\u2009=\u20090</span>. </li><li> Or he can set <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>a</i><sub class=\"lower-index\">1</sub>\u2009=\u2009\u2009-\u200919</span>. Then <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>Q</i>(<i>x</i>)\u2009=\u200910\u2009-\u200919<i>x</i>\u2009-\u20093<i>x</i><sup class=\"upper-index\">2</sup>\u2009+\u20095<i>x</i><sup class=\"upper-index\">3</sup></span> and indeed <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>Q</i>(2)\u2009=\u200910\u2009-\u200938\u2009-\u200912\u2009+\u200940\u2009=\u20090</span>. </li></ol><p>In the second sample, we are given the same polynomial. This time though, <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>k</i></span> is equal to <span class=\"tex-span\">12</span> instead of <span class=\"tex-span\">10<sup class=\"upper-index\">9</sup></span>. Two first of ways listed above are still valid but in the third way we would get <span class=\"tex-span\">|<i>a</i><sub class=\"lower-index\">1</sub>|\u2009&gt;\u2009<i>k</i></span> what is not allowed. Thus, the answer is <span class=\"tex-span\">2</span> this time.</p>",
